cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with reinforcement learning and proposes a method for disentangling options. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RL is a subfield of AI. Additionally, the paper discusses statistical indicators, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of the option-critic architecture suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
